ions. In deconstructing the assumptions of linear continuity between traditional and contemporary movements, Bishara details various divergences in both doctrine and context of modern Salafisms, plural. On Salafism is a crucial read for those interested in Islamism, jihadism, and Middle East politics and history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aIslam and politics. 0aReligious fanaticism. 0aSalafīyah. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Rituals & Practice.2bisacsh  aArab states.  aHanbalism.  aISIL.  aIslam.  aIslamic theology.  aJihadis.  aSalafis.  aWahhabism.  areligiosity.  areligious movements.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363179340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631793/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles